examples.en: The culture has been corrupted by Western influences.
Young people are often corrupted by bad books. (Fordyce)
They spoke a corrupted version of the language.
The file has been corrupted and no longer works properly.
The original file was corrupted, so they had to reenter the data.
Young prisoners are being corrupted by the older, long-term offenders.
Their idealism has been corrupted by cynicism.
